import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'])
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['speed'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Speed')
    plt.axvline(data['speed'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['speed'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Speed')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of speed?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    dirCat_counts = data['dirCat'].value_counts()
    dirCat_counts.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'green', 'red', 'cyan', 'magenta', 'yellow', 'black', 'white'])
    
    plt.title('How does the direction of travel vary across the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Direction Categories')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(dirCat_counts.index, title='Direction Categories', loc='upper right')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['dir'], data['speed'], c=data['dirCat'].astype('category').cat.codes, cmap='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('Direction')
    plt.ylabel('Speed')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between speed and direction?', wrap=True)
    plt.colorbar().set_label('Direction Category')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    avg_speed_by_dirCat = data.groupby('dirCat')['speed'].mean()
    ax = avg_speed_by_dirCat.plot(kind='bar', color='blue', legend=True)
    plt.title('What is the average speed for each direction category?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Direction Category')
    plt.ylabel('Average Speed')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Average Speed'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
